0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fus%2Fwith-gallic-shrug-fed-bids-adieu-recession-that-wasnt-2023-08-16%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DReuters%2520polls%2520of%2520economists%2520over%2Cmost%2520recent%2520read%253A%252055%2525.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%2065%25%20of%20the%20economists%20it%20surveyed%20said%20a%20recession%20would%20arrive%20in%20the%20following%2012%20months.%20Things%20were%20supposed%20to%20get%20ugly%2C%20and%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20to%20today%20and%20the%20sun%20is%20still%20shining%20on%20the%20US%20economy.%20Unemployment%20is%20below%204%25%2C%20inflation%20is%20sliding%2C%20consumers%20are%20still%20spending%2C%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20rallied%20as%20much%20as%2020%25%20this%20year%20before%20cooling%20off%20recently.%20And%20the%20GDP%20is%20projected%20to%20grow%20by%201.6%25%20in%20this%20third%20quarter%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philadelphiafed.org%2Fsurveys-and-data%2Freal-time-data-research%2Fspf-q3-2023%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520U.S.%2520economy%2520for%2520the%2Cpercent%2520in%2520the%2520last%2520survey.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomists%20surveyed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Philadelphia%20Fed%20said.%20Hardly%20recession%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOptimistic%2C%20bullish%20economists%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-recession-stock-market-crash-calls-wrong-economy-housing-2023-6%5C%22%3E%20are%20of%20course%20relishing%20the%20opportunity%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20say%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20you%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20consensus%20starts%20to%20bend%20toward%20their%20view%20that%20the%20economy%20will%20achieve%20a%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%94%20lower%20inflation%20without%20the%20need%20for%20an%20economic%20shock%20like%20a%20recession.%20Economists%20at%20Bank%20of%20America%20and%20JPMorgan%20now%20say%20a%20recession%20will%20not%20happen%20this%20year%2C%20or%20perhaps%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20the%20economy's%20flight%20path%20seems%20gentle%20now%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20there%20won't%20be%20turbulence%20ahead.%20According%20to%20top%20Wall%20Street%20strategists%20and%20economists%20I've%20spoken%20with%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20evidence%20that%20a%20recession%20is%20on%20the%20way.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20bulls%20are%20declaring%20victory%20far%20too%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20say%20today%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20a%20soft%20landing%20is%20so%20premature%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Kantrowitz%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20at%20Piper%20Sandler%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHistory%20tells%20you%20you%20really%20can't%20make%20that%20assessment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELong%20and%20variable%20lags%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fulcrum%20on%20which%20much%20of%20the%20economy%20pivots%20is%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20interest-rate%20policies.%20Higher%20interest%20rates%20for%20various%20types%20of%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20mortgages%2C%20auto%20loans%2C%20and%20credit%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20hamper%20people's%20ability%20to%20afford%20purchases%20big%20and%20small%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20weigh%20on%20businesses'%20ability%20to%20borrow.%20In%20theory%2C%20these%20higher%20interest%20rates%20push%20down%20demand%20and%20slow%20inflation%20by%20forcing%20companies%20to%20cut%20prices%20to%20attract%20stretched-thin%20customers.%20Lower%20interest%20rates%20work%20in%20the%20reverse%2C%20stimulating%20the%20economy%20by%20making%20it%20cheaper%20to%20borrow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20onslaught%20of%20interest-rate%20increases%20over%20the%20past%2016%20months%20%E2%80%94%20going%20from%20near%20zero%20to%205.5%25%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Brecession%20is%20coming%26quot%3B%20argument%20all%20along.%20The%20current%20hiking%20cycle%20is%20the%20fastest%20and%20most%20aggressive%20since%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20and%20this%20historic%20increase%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20was%20supposed%20to%20put%20the%20brakes%20on%20demand%2C%20slow%20consumer%20spending%2C%20hurt%20corporate%20earnings%2C%20and%20cost%20people%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20this%20hard%20reboot%2C%20however%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20been%20through%20more%20of%20a%20soft%20reset.%20Inflation%20as%20measured%20by%20the%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20has%20fallen%20from%20its%20year-over-year%20peak%20of%209.1%25%20in%20June%202022%20to%203.2%25%20as%20of%20July.%20And%20Americans%20have%20been%20spending%20right%20through%20the%20higher%20interest%20rates%3A%20Personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20and%20retail%20sales%20numbers%20have%20continued%20to%20forge%20upward.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20seemed%20to%20shake%20off%20the%20Fed%20so%20far%2C%20but%20experts%20say%20that%20higher%20cost%20of%20debt%20will%20eventually%20bite.%20As%20the%20legendary%20economist%20Milton%20Friedman%20famously%20said%20interest%20rate%20changes%20have%20%26quot%3Blong%20and%20variable%20lags%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20it%20takes%20time%20for%20the%20changes%20to%20work%20their%20way%20to%20households%20and%20businesses.%20Bob%20Doll%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20Crossmark%20Global%20Investments%20and%20a%20former%20chief%20US%20equity%20strategist%20at%20BlackRock%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20full%20impact%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20think%20that%20the%20only%20consequence%20is%20that%20a%20couple%20banks%20go%20under%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20March%20for%20about%20a%20day%20and%20a%20half%2C%20and%20then%20we%20move%20on%20our%20merry%20way%2C%20I%20think%20is%20a%20little%20naive%2C%26quot%3B%20Doll%20told%20me%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20Bank%20and%20other%20regional%20banks.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDavid%20Rosenberg%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Rosenberg%20Research%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20to%20sense%20the%20cataclysm%20that%20turned%20into%20the%202008%20recession.%20He's%20been%20calling%20for%20a%20recession%20since%20last%20year%20and%20told%20me%20that%20despite%20the%20more%20upbeat%20recent%20data%2C%20a%20downturn%20is%20still%20on%20the%20way.%20Rosenberg%20noted%20that%20the%20average%20time%20from%20the%20Fed's%20first%20interest-rate%20hike%20in%20a%20cycle%20to%20the%20start%20of%20a%20recession%20is%20about%2015%20months%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20current%20hiking%20cycle%20has%20been%20going%20for%2016.%20But%20as%20was%20the%20case%20in%20the%202008%20recession%2C%20things%20look%20like%20they're%20playing%20out%20over%20a%20bit%20longer%20timeline%20in%20this%20cycle.%20When%20the%20economy%20dipped%20into%20recession%20in%20December%202007%2C%20it%20had%20been%203%20%C2%BD%20years%20since%20the%20Fed%20started%20to%20raise%20rates%20in%20July%202004.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F2hMe2%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Effective%20federal%20funds%20rate%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20thinks%20the%20longer%20lag%20this%20time%20around%20is%20due%20to%20fiscal%20stimulus%20that%20was%20sent%20out%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20The%20amount%20of%20cushion%20the%20stimulus%20checks%20and%20other%20aid%20provided%20means%20that%20people%20can%20stomach%20higher%20interest%20rates%20for%20a%20while%20and%20consumers%20can%20adopt%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-recession-yolo-spenders-pandemic-stimulus-cash-david-rosenberg-2023-7%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BYOLO%26quot%3B%20(you%20only%20live%20once)%20attitude%20about%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20eventually%2C%20this%20attitude%20will%20wane%20as%20people%20realize%20that%20the%20higher%20rates%20aren't%20a%20flash%20in%20the%20pan.%20Even%20now%2C%20the%20number%20of%20Americans%20falling%20behind%20on%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-record-high-pandemic-spending-savings-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20starting%20to%20rise%20%E2%80%94%207.2%25%20of%20credit-card%20debt%20is%20now%20considered%20delinquent%2C%20up%20from%20just%20over%204%25%20in%202021.%20In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20that%20number%20reached%20as%20high%20as%20about%2014%25.%20Auto%20loan%20and%20mortgage%20delinquencies%20are%20also%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20others%2C%20the%20lagged%20effect%20of%20inflation%20itself%20will%20weigh%20on%20consumers%20and%20help%20tip%20the%20economy%20into%20recession.%20Tom%20Essaye%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sevens%20Report%20Research%2C%20which%20counts%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20institutions%20on%20Wall%20Street%20among%20its%20clients%2C%20said%20while%20inflation%20on%20a%20year-over-year%20basis%20has%20come%20down%20significantly%2C%20the%20cumulative%20price%20increases%20we've%20seen%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%20will%20eventually%20force%20consumers%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20get%20very%20excited%20about%20CPI%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20CPI%20went%20up%20only%200.1%25%20over%20the%20past%20month%20and%20it's%20only%20up%203%25%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C'%26quot%3B%20Essaye%20said.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20think%20about%20that%20in%20practical%20terms.%20If%20I%20go%20to%20buy%20my%20kids%20a%20bag%20of%20Skittles%2C%20in%202019%20it%20cost%20%240.75.%20Now%20it%20costs%20%241.50.%20Am%20I%20supposed%20to%20get%20excited%20because%20next%20year%20it%20costs%20%241.55%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20wheels%20of%20industry%20slow%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPiper%20Sandler's%20Kantrowitz%20pointed%20to%20another%20worry%20spot%3A%20manufacturing.%20Industrial%20production%2C%20a%20measure%20of%20just%20how%20much%20stuff%20is%20coming%20out%20of%20US%20factories%2C%20is%20starting%20to%20trend%20downward.%20And%20surveys%20of%20manufacturing%20executives%2C%20like%20the%20Institute%20for%20Supply%20Management's%20Purchasing%20Managers%20Index%2C%20show%20that%20there's%20widespread%20worry%20across%20the%20industry.%20Even%20as%20the%20sector%20has%20taken%20a%20hit%2C%20rate%20hikes%20are%20still%20working%20their%20way%20into%20manufacturing%20data.%20A%20Granger%20causality%20test%2C%20which%20establishes%20the%20highest%20point%20of%20correlation%20between%20two%20datasets%2C%20showed%20that%20it%20usually%20takes%20about%2018%20months%20for%20rate%20hikes%20to%20fully%20show%20up%20in%20manufacturing%20data.%20That%20means%20more%20downside%20is%20likely%20ahead.%20While%20manufacturing%20is%20just%20one%20portion%20of%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20experts%20say%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20watch%20because%20it's%20a%20reflection%20of%20consumer%20demand%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20a%20thermometer%20for%20the%20broader%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20lagged%20effect%20of%20the%20rate%20hikes%20is%20the%20impact%20of%20tighter%20lending%20standards%3A%20Even%20if%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20are%20interested%20in%20taking%20out%20loans%2C%20banks%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20give%20them.%20According%20to%20the%20Fed's%20Senior%20Loan%20Officer%20Opinion%20Survey%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20banks%20are%20tightening%20lending%20standards%20for%20businesses%2C%20and%20that's%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20supply%20of%20commercial%20and%20industrial%20loans%2C%20which%20have%20been%20falling%20since%20December.%20When%20this%20happens%2C%20it%20can%20mean%20banks%20are%20getting%20more%20worried%20about%20borrowers'%20ability%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20loans%20amid%20economic%20uncertainty.%20Businesses%20use%20these%20loans%20to%20grow%20and%20to%20pay%20employees%2C%20meaning%20a%20drop%20in%20loan%20issuances%20weighs%20on%20employment%20and%20business%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0TxDY%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Commercial%20and%20industrial%20loans%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Kantrowitz%20and%20Rosenberg%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20that%20think%20policy%20lags%20are%20still%20playing%20out.%20Rosenberg%20pointed%20to%20statements%20from%20the%20Fed%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20at%20a%20July%20press%20conference%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20covered%20a%20lot%20of%20ground%2C%20and%20the%20full%20effects%20of%20our%20tightening%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20felt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELagging%20realization%20for%20investors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20the%20Fed%20has%20hiked%20interest%20rates%20and%20not%20caused%20a%20recession.%20But%20these%20instances%20have%20been%20anomalous%20%E2%80%94%2080%25%20of%20Fed%20hiking%20cycles%20since%20World%20War%20II%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20recession.%20Hardly%20an%20encouraging%20track%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20key%20differentiating%20factor%2C%20Rosenberg%20said%2C%20that%20will%20indicate%20whether%20the%20economy%20is%20on%20the%20path%20to%20a%20true%20soft%20landing%20or%20will%20end%20up%20in%20a%20recession%3A%20the%20interest%20rates%20on%20different%20kinds%20of%20Treasurys.%20The%20Treasury%20yield%20curve%20measures%20the%20different%20interest%20rates%20that%20are%20paid%20out%20on%20various%20bonds%20issued%20by%20the%20US%20government.%20Usually%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%20on%20short-dated%20Treasuries%20%E2%80%94%20bonds%20that%20pay%20investors%20in%20less%20than%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20are%20lower%20than%20yields%20on%20far-out%20bonds%20like%20the%2010-year%20Treasury.%20But%20when%20that%20flips%20and%20interest%20rates%20on%20short-term%20Treasurys%20are%20higher%20than%20their%20long-term%20cousins%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20a%20yield-curve%20inversion%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20sure%20sign%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20Rosenberg%20said.%20That's%20because%20it's%20a%20sign%20that%20investors%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20economy's%20stability%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months%20and%20are%20seeking%20safety%20in%20long-term%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FxOxi1%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%2210-year%2F3-month%20treasury%20yield%20spread%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20recession%20does%20come%2C%20investors%20are%20likely%20in%20for%20a%20tough%20period%20ahead.%20As%20Rosenberg%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20stock%20market%20is%20priced%20for%20perfection.%26quot%3B%20And%20there%20are%20many%20indications%20that%20this%20is%20true.%20Sentiment%20indicators%20and%20valuation%20measures%20currently%20show%20that%20investors%20are%20expecting%20continued%20growth%20ahead.%20Kantrowitz%20pointed%20out%20that%20this%20year's%20rally%20is%20one%20of%20the%20sharpest%20over%20the%20past%2025%20years%2C%20but%20it's%20detached%20from%20fundamentals.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20market%20is%20soaring%20despite%20forward-earnings%20expectations%20being%20negative%20and%20manufacturing%20remaining%20in%20contraction%20territory.%20It's%20the%20same%20story%20every%20time%2C%20both%20Kantrowitz%20and%20Rosenberg%20say%3A%20Investors%20are%20bad%20at%20pricing%20in%20a%20recession%20before%20it%20unfolds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20stocks%20fall%20in%20a%20recessionary%20scenario%20probably%20depends%20on%20the%20depth%20of%20the%20downturn.%20Doll%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20only%20sees%20a%20mild%20recession%20ahead%2C%20and%20therefore%20sees%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20likely%20falling%20as%20much%20as%20another%2013%25.%20But%20in%20the%20past%2013%20recessions%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20dropped%20an%20average%20of%2032%25%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww6.royalbank.com%2Fen%2Fdi%2Fhubs%2Fnow-and-noteworthy%2Farticle%2Fwhat-does-a-recession-mean-for-the-markets%2Fl41dzgqb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Royal%20Bank%20of%20Canada%20noted.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20current%20strength%20of%20the%20market%2C%20a%20recent%20summer%20swoon%20notwithstanding%2C%20most%20investors%20assume%20that%20the%20optimists%20are%20right%3A%20Inflation%20is%20going%20to%20stay%20low%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20will%20hold%20up%2C%20and%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20interest-rate%20hikes%20are%20in%20the%20rearview%20mirror.%20But%20when%20markets%20get%20complacent%2C%20Kantrowitz%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bhistorically%2C%20people%20have%20gotten%20in%20trouble%20every%20single%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fwilliam-edwards%5C%22%3EWilliam%20Edwards%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20investing%20reporter%20at%20Insider%20covering%20the%20US%20stock%20market%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-still-headed-for-recession-stock-market-crash-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692696362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e3cd27b698ac0019de93e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-still-headed-for-recession-stock-market-crash-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leading%20economists%20say%20the%20threat%20of%20recession%20has%20passed%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20reasons%20to%20think%20the%20worst%20is%20yet%20to%20come.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-still-headed-for-recession-stock-market-crash-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Gives%20Assurance%20As%20Asia's%20Largest%20Onion%20Market%20Shut%20For%20Second%20Day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20centre%20on%20Tuesday%20offered%20assurances%20to%20farmers%20and%20traders%20protesting%20the%20decision%20to%20impose%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-imposes-40-duty-on-onion-exports-till-december-31-4311717%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40%20per%20cent%20export%20duty%20on%20onions%3C%2Fa%3E%20-%20a%20move%20it%20believes%20will%20check%20increase%20in%20prices%20of%20the%20kitchen%20staple%20in%20domestic%20markets%20-%20and%20said%20it%20had%20begun%20purchasing%20unsold%20stocks%20at%20the%20'historic'%20price%20of%20Rs%202%2C410%20per%20quintal.%20The%20centre%20plans%20to%20procure%20around%20two%20lakh%20tonnes%20extra%20-%20around%20three%20lakh%20tonnes%20have%20already%20been%20purchased%20-%20in%20buffer%20stocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20media%20briefing%20today%2C%20union%20commerce%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20confirmed%20procurement%20had%20started%20and%20slammed%20'political%20opponents'%20for%20'trying%20to%20present%20a%20wrong%20picture%20(about%20export%20curbs)'.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20urge%20all%20farmers%20in%20onion%20producing%20states%20not%20to%20indulge%20in%20any%20panic%20selling%2C%26quot%3B%20Goyal%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNCCF%20(National%20Cooperative%20Consumers'%20Federation)%20and%20NAFED%20(National%20Agricultural%20Cooperative%20Marketing%20Federation%20of%20India)%20have%20been%20directed%20to%20procure%20onions...%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20agriculture%20minister%20Dhananjay%20Munde%20told%20NDTV%20the%20decision%20to%20procure%20onions%20was%20made%20after%20deputy%20chief%20ministers%20Ajit%20Pawar%20and%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20and%20he%20spoke%20to%20Goyal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-exports-dada-bhuse-amid-protests-over-export-duty-on-onions-maharashtra-ministers-shocker-4317924%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_topstories%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmid%20Protests%20Over%20Export%20Duty%20On%20Onions%2C%20Maharashtra%20Minister's%20Shocker%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20farmers%20were%20worried%20about%20the%2040%20per%20cent%20duty%20imposed%20on%20the%20export%20of%20onions%20(they%20felt)%20that%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fonion-prices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonion%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20falling%20in%20the%20(domestic)%20market.%20Keeping%20in%20view%20their%20sentiment%20and%20their%20need%2C%20he%20(Goyal)%20took%20a%20historic%20decision%20-%20wherever%20farmers%20grow%20onions%20in%20the%20country...%20last%20year%2C%20NCCF%20and%20NAFED%20bought%20onions%20at%20Rs%201%2C200%20per%20quintal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EOnion%20farmers'%20protests%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20assurances%20come%20after%20two%20days%20of%20protests%20in%20Nashik%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20where%20onion%20auctions%20were%20closed%20indefinitely%2C%20at%20all%20APMCs%20(Agriculture%20Produce%20Market%20Committees)%2C%20including%20at%20Lasalgaon%20-%20the%20largest%20wholesale%20onion%20market%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20told%20news%20agency%20PTI%20a%20furious%20onion%20traders'%20association%20in%20Nashik%20said%20it%20will%20not%20take%20part%20in%20auctions%20of%20the%20vegetable%20till%20the%20union%20government%20rolled%20back%20the%2040%20per%20cent%20export%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20say%20bad%20weather%20has%20impacted%20half%20their%20produce%20and%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20government%20for%20failing%20to%20act%20when%20they%20face%20catastrophic%20losses.%20%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20get%20any%20assistance%20from%20the%20government%20last%20time.%C2%A0Around%20Rs%2020%20have%20been%20spent%20per%20kilo%20by%20farmers...%20they%20demand%20Rs%2040%20per%20kg%20rate.%C2%A0Not%20every%20farmer%20is%20able%20to%20sell%20the%20produce%20via%20NAFED%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20farmer%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20the%20export%20duty%20on%20onions%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2040%20per%20cent%20export%20duty%20on%20onions%20-%20effective%20till%20December%2031%20and%20meant%20to%20restrict%20outward%20shipments%20and%20boost%20local%20availability%20of%20the%20vegetable%20-%20was%20announced%20last%20week.%20It%20was%20also%20decided%20to%20increase%20buffer%20stocks%20from%20three%20lakh%20tonnes%20to%20five%20lakh%20tonnes%20for%20the%202023-24%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-export-duty-timely-move-to-boost-domestic-supply-top-official-4316568%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnion%20Export%20Duty%20%26quot%3BTimely%26quot%3B%20Move%20To%20Boost%20Domestic%20Supply%3A%20Top%20Official%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERabi%20onion%20harvested%20during%20April-June%20accounts%20for%2065%20per%20cent%20of%20India's%20onion%20production%20and%20meets%20the%20consumer's%20demand%20till%20the%20kharif%20crop%20is%20harvested%20in%20October-November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAfter%20tomatoes%2C%20onions%20sold%20at%20subsidised%20prices%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%20NCCF%20outlets%20began%20retail%20sale%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FOnion%2520To%2520Be%2520Sold%2520At%2520Subsidised%2520Rate%2520Of%2520Rs%252025%2FKg%2520In%2520Delhi%2520From%2520Monday%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonions%20at%20subsidised%20prices%20of%20Rs%2025%20per%20kg%20in%20the%20national%20capital%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20NCCF%20is%20already%20selling%20tomatoes%20at%20subsidised%20rates.%20The%20government%20has%20also%20identified%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Assam%20for%20market%20intervention%20and%20availability%20is%20being%20enhanced%20in%20these%20states%20by%20releasing%20buffer%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20input%20from%20PTI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692696300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fitqca4qg_onion_625x300_21_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-prices-40-export-duty-centre-gives-assurance-rs-2410-per-quintal-as-nashik-onion-market-shut-for-second-day-4318629%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Union%20Commerce%20Minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20said%20procurement%20of%20onion%20crops%20at%20the%20'historic'%20price%20of%20Rs%202%2C410%20per%20quintal%20-%20a%20move%20in%20response%20to%20protests%20by%20farmers%20over%20the%2040%20per%20cent%20export%20duty%20on%20the%20staple%20vegetable%20-%20began%20at%20noon%20on%20Tuesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-prices-40-export-duty-centre-gives-assurance-rs-2410-per-quintal-as-nashik-onion-market-shut-for-second-day-4318629%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-prices-40-export-duty-centre-gives-assurance-rs-2410-per-quintal-as-nashik-onion-market-shut-for-second-day-4318629%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fonion-prices-40-export-duty-centre-gives-assurance-rs-2410-per-quintal-as-nashik-onion-market-shut-for-second-day-4318629%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Jawan'%20brings%20international%20action%20directors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692696189000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fthumb%2Fmsid-102940850%2Cwidth-1070%2Cheig