22%20at%20the%20Airthings%20Masters%20(an%20online%20rapid%20chess%20tournament).%20Cut%20to%20May%202022%20and%20the%20youngster%20was%20once%20again%20the%20victor%20against%20Carlsen%20at%20the%20Chessable%20Masters%20online%20rapid%20chess%20tournament%20%E2%80%93%20a%20win%20that%20earned%20him%20a%20lot%20of%20praise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20biggest%20achievement%20for%20Praggnanandhaa%20came%20exactly%20one%20year%20ago%20when%20he%20defeated%20Carlsen%20in%20three%20consecutive%20games%20%E2%80%94%20one%20rapid%20and%20two%20blitz%20%E2%80%94%20at%202022%20FTX%20Crypto%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692694680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F3seo64s8_edfwe_625x300_22_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fchess%2Fchess-world-cup-final-a-look-at-r-praggnanandhaas-record-against-magnus-carlsen-4318628%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22R%20Praggnanandhaa%20faces%20Magnus%20Carlsen%20in%20the%20final%20of%20the%20Chess%20World%20Cup%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fchess%2Fchess-world-cup-final-a-look-at-r-praggnanandhaas-record-against-magnus-carlsen-4318628%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fchess%2Fchess-world-cup-final-a-look-at-r-praggnanandhaas-record-against-magnus-carlsen-4318628%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fchess%2Fchess-world-cup-final-a-look-at-r-praggnanandhaas-record-against-magnus-carlsen-4318628%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20company%20lost%20%24450K%20because%20we%20didn't%20fire%205%20wrong%20hires%20quickly%20enough.%20It's%20important%20to%20'fire%20fast'%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it's%20difficult.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Melissa%20Kwan%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20eWebinar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e3b295bd98a600197b373b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelissa%20Kwan%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20eWebinar%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Kwan%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De8301967eccb9d27ea678ca38d34e3a99a325637d02ba4ff553204f209cc0b15%26postID%3D64de7b7bf87b369c6da2800e%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fmelissakwan_we-made-5-wrong-hires-that-ended-up-costing-activity-7085241513718231040-lGhM%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMelissa%20Kwan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20eWebinar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20that%20it%20may%20seem%20simple%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20struggle%20to%C2%A0%26quot%3Bhire%20slow%2C%20fire%20fast.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKwan%20writes%20that%20you%20need%20to%20trust%20your%20gut%20and%20learn%20to%20separate%20emotion%20from%20decisions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20challenge%20in%20building%20companies%20hasn't%20been%20product%2C%20sales%2C%20or%20marketing.%20It's%20been%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20so%20difficult%20to%20hire%20great%20people.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20working%20with%20someone%20just%20because%20it%20was%20easier%20than%20having%20to%20find%20someone%20new%2C%20even%20when%20I%20knew%20in%20my%20heart%20they%20were%20not%20the%20right%20fit%20for%20us.%20After%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20and%20money%20because%20I'd%20rather%20avoid%20tough%20conversations%2C%20I%20finally%20learned%20the%20importance%20of%20%26quot%3Bfiring%20fast%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bhire%20slow%2C%20fire%20fast%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20popularized%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-unwritten-rules-of-working-at-a-startup-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estartup%20culture%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20agility%20required%20to%20grow%20a%20company%20in%20a%20competitive%20environment.%3C%2Fa%3E%20While%20this%20concept%20may%20seem%20simple%20and%20obvious%2C%20it%20requires%20confidence%2C%20clarity%2C%20and%20maturity%20to%20put%20it%20into%20practice.%20Even%20as%20a%203X%20founder%20myself%2C%20it's%20a%20constant%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fewebinar.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EeWebinar%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20webinar%20automation%20solution%20that%20helps%20companies%20run%20hundreds%20of%20webinars%20without%20needing%20to%20be%20there%20to%20host%20them%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20bootstrapped%20three%20startups%20over%20the%20last%2013%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-bootstrap-startup-to-success-according-to-founders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBootstrappers%20like%20me%20are%20entrepreneurs%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewho%20found%20startups%20without%20institutional%20capital%2C%20such%20as%20venture%20capital%20or%20private%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20first%20two%20years%2C%20we%20made%20five%20wrong%20hires%20that%20ended%20up%20costing%20%24450k%20because%20we%20didn't%20%26quot%3Bfire%20fast%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%26quot%3BFire%20fast%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20mean%20literally%20removing%20someone%20on%20the%20spot%20at%20a%20moment%20of%20doubt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20don't%20try%20your%20best%20to%20work%20with%20the%20person%20for%20a%20reasonable%20amount%20of%20time%20or%20that%20you%20didn't%20have%20multiple%20conversations%20leading%20up%20to%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20having%20the%20awareness%20and%20conviction%20to%20know%20when%20you%20need%20to%20move%20on%20because%20it's%20not%20working%20out.%20Sometimes%20it's%20us%2C%20sometimes%20it's%20them%2C%20sometimes%20it's%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20have%20that%20hard%20conversation%20with%20someone%20you%20like%20because%20it's%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do%20for%20the%20company%20and%20their%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20you%20need%20to%20listen%20to%20your%20gut%2C%20separating%20your%20emotions%2C%20and%20being%20honest%20about%20missed%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20five%20companies%20or%20people%20that%20we%20should%20have%20parted%20ways%20with%20much%20sooner%20than%20we%20did%20and%20what%20it's%20cost%20us%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Dev%20shop%20that%20underestimated%20our%20project%3A%20%24250k%20over%2010%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Bdev%20shop%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20software%20development%20agency%20that%20offers%20services%20to%20tech%20companies%20for%20building%20software.%20I%20had%20hired%20a%20dev%20shop%20to%20be%20my%20%26quot%3BCTO%26quot%3B%20because%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20needed%20a%20cofounder.%20They%20were%20supposed%20to%20build%20our%20version%20one%20before%20we%20outsourced%20the%20product%20development%20to%20another%20team.%20They%20didn't%20have%20enough%20experience%20building%20platforms%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20at%20the%20time%20and%20unintentionally%20underestimated%20the%20project%20size%20and%20capabilities%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20it%20was%20a%20friend's%20company%2C%20I%20didn't%20question%20things%20as%20early%20as%20I%20should%20have.%20I%20realize%20now%20how%20naive%20it%20was%20to%20attempt%20building%20a%20startup%20without%20a%20technical%20cofounder%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20my%20CTO%2FCofounder%20and%20I%20came%20together.%20All%20things%20considered%2C%20this%20was%20a%20happy%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Convenient%20person%20we%20could%20afford%3A%20%245k%20over%202%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20we%20were%20bootstrapped%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20needed%20to%20make%20concessions%20by%20hiring%20who%20we%20could%20afford%20instead%20of%20the%20best%20person%20for%20the%20task.%20Every%20time%20we%20compromised%20on%20quality%2C%20we%20had%20to%20do%20it%20again.%20Now%2C%20we%20only%20hire%20people%20who%20are%20best%20for%20the%20job%2C%20we%20never%20negotiate%20on%20their%20fees.%20If%20we%20can't%20afford%20them%2C%20we%20either%20move%20on%2C%20or%20we%20have%20a%20discussion%20to%20reduce%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20project%20such%20that%20we%20both%20benefit.%20Someone%20else's%20worth%20should%20not%20be%20dependent%20on%20our%20ability%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Agencies%20hired%20to%20fix%20the%20pain%20we%20knew%20nothing%20about%3A%20%2450k%20over%2011%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20us%20knew%20marketing%20and%20we%20were%20desperate%20to%20%26quot%3Bfix%20our%20SEO%26quot%3B%2C%20so%20we%20hired%20companies%20and%20gave%20them%20free%20rein.%20We%20wanted%20it%20to%20work%20so%20badly%20we%20convinced%20ourselves%20that%20we%20needed%20to%20give%20it%20more%20time.%20Most%20agencies%20can%20get%20you%20from%201%20to%202%20but%20not%20from%200%20to%201.%20I%20learned%20that%20you%20can't%20hire%20someone%20to%20take%20away%20your%20pain%20when%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20basic%20understanding%20of%20the%20job%20to%20be%20done.%20We%20decided%20to%20learn%20it%20ourselves%20and%20now%20own%20our%20content%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Paid%20ads%20consultants%20we%20were%20too%20early%20for%3A%20%2415k%20over%209%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20early%20stage%20startup%20should%20be%20spending%20money%20on%20paid%20ads%20because%20the%20product%20is%20too%20immature%20and%20the%20company%20doesn't%20have%20credibility%20yet.%20I%20didn't%20know%20that%2C%20coming%20from%20a%20sales-led%20background%20(where%20sales%20are%20made%20through%20face-to-face%20meetings).%20We%20wanted%20to%20drive%20trial%20sign%20ups%20so%20we%20thought%20we'd%20give%20paid%20acquisition%20a%20try.%20Consultants%20told%20us%20it's%20never%20too%20early%20and%20they%20can%20experiment%20with%20very%20little%20and%20charge%20a%20retainer%20on%20top.%20Lesson%20learned%3A%20when%20your%20product%20category%20is%20immature%20and%20people%20can't%20immediately%20grasp%20how%20your%20product%20drives%20value%20for%20them%2C%20paying%20for%20ads%20is%20a%20waste%20of%20money.%20It's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20shiny%20taglines%20and%20catchy%20copy%20to%20convert%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Executive%20who%20only%20worked%20for%20big%20companies%3A%20%24130k%20over%2012%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20brought%20someone%20on%20board%20who%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20success%20in%20big%2C%20well-resourced%2C%20slow-moving%20companies.%20Working%20for%20startups%20requires%20scrappiness%20and%20agility%20that%20people%20from%20corporate%20typically%20don't%20have.%20Because%20he%20took%20a%2050%25%20pay%20cut%20to%20join%20our%20team%20and%20was%20a%20friend%2C%20I%20felt%20personally%20liable%20for%20his%20success%20and%20tried%20too%20hard%20for%20too%20long%20to%20make%20it%20work.%20This%20one%20was%20most%20painful%20because%20it%20also%20cost%20me%20a%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20expensive%20thing%20about%20wrong%20hires%20is%20not%20money%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20TIME%20(and%20sadly%20sometimes%20friendships%2C%20as%20mentioned%20above).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20all%20costs%20can%20be%20avoided%20%E2%80%94%20because%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20don't%20know%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20be%20mitigated%20by%20%26quot%3Bfiring%20fast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiring%20fast%20lets%20you%20to%20do%20two%20things%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Cut%20your%20losses%2C%20change%20strategies%20or%20find%20someone%20more%20suited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Let%20the%20person%20go%20and%20find%20another%20role%20that's%20better%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20doesn't%20make%20you%20ruthless%20%E2%80%94%20It%20makes%20you%20discerning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20light%20of%20massive%20layoffs%2C%20this%20is%20a%20sensitive%20topic%20as%20that%20phrase%20carries%20a%20negative%20connotation.%20It%20reinforced%20the%20idea%20that%20employers%20are%20evil%20and%20leaders%20don't%20care%20about%20their%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20there%20are%20CEOs%20making%20millions%20while%20their%20employees%20are%20on%20strike%20just%20to%20fight%20for%20fair%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20there%20are%20CEOs%20on%20the%20world's%20richest%20list%20who%20are%20allegedly%20not%20paying%20and%20treating%20workers%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20multiple%20bloated%20startups%20over%20hired%20to%20hoard%20talent%20because%20they%20could%2C%20then%20mass%20fired%20when%20they%20failed%20to%20build%20a%20business%20to%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20that%20behavior%20is%20appalling.%20But%20most%20companies%20in%20this%20world%20are%20NOT%20those%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20companies%2C%20like%20mine%2C%20are%20small%20businesses.%20Regular%20people%20working%20hard%20to%20make%20a%20living%20by%20building%20something%20valuable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20compete%20against%20those%20juggernauts%2C%20we%20need%20to%20inspire%20people%20to%20join%20our%20team%20by%20treating%20them%20like%20family%20and%20giving%20them%20everything%20within%20our%20power%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20happy%20because%20we%20cannot%20compete%20on%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20doesn't%20work%20out%2C%20the%20pain%20is%20felt%20deeply.%20It's%20not%20just%20money%20for%20us.%20It's%20the%20emotional%20investment%20we%20put%20into%20every%20single%20team%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20bootstrapped%20company%2C%20every%20dollar%20we%20spend%20is%20precious%20because%20we%20are%20constantly%20making%20concessions%20somewhere%20else.%20Every%20dollar%20going%20to%20the%20wrong%20thing%20is%20a%20dollar%20not%20going%20to%20the%20right%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20everyone%20needs%20to%20understand%20about%20working%20with%20a%20startup%2C%20especially%20non-venture-backed%20ones.%20This%20is%20why%20%26quot%3Bfiring%20fast%26quot%3B%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe've%20learned%20to%20focus%20on%20hiring%20slow%2C%20and%20only%20hiring%20the%20best%20person%20for%20the%20role%2C%20or%20we%20don't%20hire%20at%20all%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20onboard%20a%20new%20team%20member%2C%20we%20ask%20that%20they%20tell%20us%20the%20moment%20they're%20thinking%20about%20%26quot%3Bfiring%26quot%3B%20us%20so%20we%20can%20have%20an%20honest%20conversation%20about%20it%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFiring%20fast%26quot%3B%20carries%20a%20negative%20connotation%20because%20it%20sounds%20dismissive%20and%20brutal.%20But%20the%20reality%20of%20those%20two%20words%20is%20often%20the%20opposite%20because%20it's%20likely%20that%20we%20fought%20long%20and%20hard%20for%20that%20person%20before%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20difficult%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20painful.%20But%20it's%20a%20concept%20we%20needed%20to%20learn%20because%20what%20makes%20a%20business%20successful%20is%20the%20team%20behind%20it.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D86944c7fa3ebf2ef9387b679519f51557a0e3899f027c556b2f5fba7f11553de%26postID%3D64de7b7bf87b369c6da2800e%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fin%252Fmelissakwan%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMelissa%20Kwan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20eWebinar.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-hires-cost-us-nearly-500k-didnt-fire-fast-enough-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692694501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e3b29eb698ac0019de6fdf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-hires-cost-us-nearly-500k-didnt-fire-fast-enough-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Melissa%20Kwan%20is%20a%20CEO%20who%20says%20that%20every%20dollar%20her%20startup%20spends%20is%20precious.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Melissa%20Kwan%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-hires-cost-us-nearly-500k-didnt-fire-fast-enough-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian-Origin%20Ex-Minister%20In%20Final%203-Way%20Race%20To%20Be%20Singapore%20President%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESingapore-born%20Indian-origin%20Tharman%20Shanmugaratnam%20was%20today%20officially%20announced%20as%20a%20candidate%20for%20the%20prosperous%20city-state's%20presidential%20election%20on%20September%201%2C%20along%20with%20two%20Chinese-origin%20former%20business%20executives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharman%2C%2066%2C%20former%20investment%20chief%20of%20state-owned%20company%20Ng%20Kok%20Song%2C%2075%2C%20and%20former%20head%20of%20the%20state-run%20insurance%20company%20Tan%20Kin%20Lian%2C%2075%2C%20were%20officially%20announced%20as%20candidates%20by%20the%20Elections%20Department%20(ELD)%20for%20Singapore's%20highest%20but%20non-political%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20three%20have%20been%20officially%20announced%20as%20candidates%2C%20they%20cannot%20pull%20out%20of%20the%20race%20without%20forfeiting%20their%20election%20deposits%20of%20SGD%2040%2C500%20each%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20The%20Straits%20Times%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20men%2C%20each%20vying%20to%20become%20Singapore's%20ninth%20president%2C%20can%20officially%20begin%20campaigning%2C%20which%20will%20end%20on%20August%2030.%20The%20cooling-off%20day%20is%20on%20August%2031%2C%20and%20the%20Polling%20Day%20is%20on%20September%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingapore's%20incumbent%20President%20Halimah%20Yacob's%20six-year%20term%20will%20end%20on%20September%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20speech%20after%20the%20nomination%2C%20Mr%20Tharman%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20minister%20in%20the%20ruling%20People's%20Action%20Party%20Government%2C%20said%20he%20looked%20forward%20to%20a%20dignified%20and%20honourable%20contest%2C%20focused%20on%20what%20each%20candidate%20brings%20to%20Singaporeans%20and%20what%20each%20of%20them%20brings%20to%20the%20country's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20look%20forward%20to%20a%20campaign%2C%20which%20is%20dignified%20and%20honourable%2C%20and%20a%20campaign%20which%20itself%20seeks%20to%20unite%20Singaporeans%20and%20not%20divide%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharman%20later%20told%20the%20media%20that%20he%20was%20running%20for%20the%20presidency%20not%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20new%20positions%20or%20statements%20but%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20long-held%20purpose%20in%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20in%20a%20fairer%2C%20more%20compassionate%20and%20more%20inclusive%20society.%20And%20my%20life%20is%20dedicated%20to%20that.%20Singapore%20can%20be%20special%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20quoted%20Mr%20Tharman%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharman%2C%20who%20resigned%20from%20all%20political%20and%20public%20offices%20in%20July%20to%20contest%20for%20the%20presidency%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20our%20future%20that%20we%20are%20concerned%20about%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20different%20future%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20a%20more%20difficult%20and%20challenging%20future%20that%20we%20face%2C%20which%20is%20the%20reason%20why%20I%20have%20entered%20this%20contest%20to%20offer%20all%20my%20experience%20and%20capabilities%20on%20the%20ground%20for%20a%20few%20decades%20nationally%20and%20internationally%2C%26quot%3B%20Channel%20News%20Asia%20quoted%20Mr%20Tharman%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20that%20I%20can%20serve%20Singaporeans%20in%20the%20role%20of%20President%20with%20all%20my%20heart%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharman%20was%20an%20economist%20and%20civil%20servant%2C%20mainly%20at%20the%20Monetary%20Authority%20of%20Singapore%2C%20before%20joining%20politics%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20served%20as%20Minister%20for%20Education%20and%20Finance%20and%20was%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20from%202011%20to%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENg%2C%20who%20introduced%20himself%20in%20Chinese%2C%20Malay%20and%20Tamil%2C%20said%20he%20was%20standing%20for%20president%20to%20protect%20Singapore's%20three%20national%20treasures%20-the%20reserves%2C%20public%20service%20appointments%20and%20social%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20I'm%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20really%20serve%20the%20people%20of%20Singapore.%20So%2C%20I%20feel%20excited%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Singapore%20are%20giving%20me%20this%20opportunity%20to%20serve%20my%20country%20one%20more%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETan%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20give%20the%20people%20of%20Singapore%20%26quot%3Ba%20chance%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20president%20who%20is%20truly%20independent%20of%20the%20ruling%20government%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20if%20elected%2C%20will%20carry%20out%20his%20duties%2C%20as%20set%20out%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20diligently%2C%20honestly%2C%20and%20to%20the%20best%20of%20his%20ability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20duties%20are%20to%20safeguard%20the%20reserves%20and%20uphold%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20public%20service.%20I%20ask%20for%20your%20support%20so%20that%20I%20can%20do%20my%20best%20for%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20a%20non-political%20office%2C%20the%20President%20is%20responsible%20for%20several%20critical%20functions%20in%20the%20city-state%2C%20including%20key%20state%20appointments%20and%20guarding%20the%20national%20reserves%20that%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20can%20only%20use%20with%20presidential%20consensus.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20