%2F08%2Fmusic-7-1691673406.jpg%20550w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fmusic-7-1691673406-300x164.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fmusic-7-1691673406-500x273.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fmusic-7-1691673406-150x82.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-326982%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELata%20Mangeshkar%20sang%20Ae%20Mere%20Watan%20for%20the%20first%20time%20on%2027%20January%201963%20during%20the%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20at%20the%20National%20Stadium%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20The%20Better%20India%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20significance%20of%20this%20song%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%20is%20no%20secret.%20With%20Kavi%20Pradeep%E2%80%99s%20heart-wrenching%20lyrics%20that%20match%20the%20sombre%20beat%2C%20the%20song%20was%20one%20of%20Lata%20Mangeshkar%E2%80%99s%20best%20works%20and%20was%20sung%20by%20her%20for%20the%20first%20time%20on%2027%20January%201963%20during%20the%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20at%20the%20National%20Stadium%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Mangeshkar%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F160687%2Flata-mangeshkar-birthday-little-known%2F%5C%22%3Emellifluous%20voice%3C%2Fa%3E%20moved%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20to%20tears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20anecdote%20tells%20of%20how%20the%20idea%20for%20the%20lyrics%20came%20to%20poet%20Pradeep%20while%20he%20was%20taking%20a%20walk%20along%20Mahim%20Beach%20in%20Mumbai.%20He%20borrowed%20a%20pen%20from%20a%20fellow%20stroller%20and%20wrote%20the%20first%20stanza%20of%20the%20song%20on%20the%20foil%20from%20a%20pack%20of%20cigarettes.%20It%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20an%20ode%20to%20the%20bravery%20of%20soldiers%20who%20had%20fought%20in%20the%201962%20Indo-China%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhil